4. **Fisher Information Forecast for SKA**: Perform a Fisher matrix analysis using the differential distribution $dN/d\tau$ to estimate the sensitivity of SKA-era observations to $M_{cut}$. Assume a Poisson noise model $\sigma(dN/d\tau) = \sqrt{N_{obs}} / \Delta\tau$. Calculate the Fisher information $F_{ij} = \sum_{\tau} \frac{1}{\sigma^2} \frac{\partial (dN/d\tau)}{\partial \theta_i} \frac{\partial (dN/d\tau)}{\partial \theta_j}$, where $\theta$ represents the DM parameters. Determine the 1-$\sigma$ and 2-$\sigma$ confidence intervals for $\sigma_0/m_\chi$ at each redshift.

